&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay up to – $34/hr. based on experience and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Production Supervisor is a critical role in the success of our operation. The incumbent will be responsible for managing a team of manufacturing associates to produce high-quality products that meet or exceed run rates while maintaining a safe facility. This Supervisor will spend the majority of their time on the production floor providing guidance and decision making to achieve maximum output, low waste, minimal rejects in a consistently efficient operation. Responsibilities also include training a team of direct reports, holding team accountable for performing consistently and in a safe manner, collaborating closely with Quality Assurance, Vendor Assurance and Maintenance to meet all of the standards as well as interact with USDA as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this is a &lt;strong&gt;1st&amp;nbsp;Shift opportunity&lt;/strong&gt; with the hours of &lt;strong&gt;5:00am - 5:00pm&lt;/strong&gt; based in our Norwood, MA manufacturing facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute daily production schedules, ensuring efficient use of labor and resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop employees while managing staffing, attendance, and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor production processes to ensure quality standards and product specifications are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain proper raw material levels and accurate production reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and address safety concerns; ensure compliance with OSHA, HACCP, USDA, and plant standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train team members and support ongoing skill development and cross-training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to resolve production issues and improve workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement initiatives to enhance efficiency and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain shift logs, training records, and operational data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee plant sanitation activities, ensuring compliance with standards and supporting sanitation schedules (including weekends/non-production days as needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise post-sanitation startup to ensure safety, quality, and operational readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate degree or equivalent experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of supervisory experience in manufacturing (food production strongly preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with production processes, quality standards, and safety compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate material handling equipment (forklift/pallet jack)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual (Spanish or Portuguese) a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment &amp;amp; Physical Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular presence in production areas, including cold, wet, humid, and noisy environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to walk production floors, climb ladders and stairs, and occasionally lift up to 50 pounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frequently required to stand; walk; use hands to handle or feel; reach with hands and arms; stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl and talk or hear&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Off-shift and weekend work may be required to support breakdowns, shutdowns, or project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strict adherence to safety, PPE, and hygiene standards is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
